                 CALENDAR - Help Screen     To select a function, press [CLEAR] and the function number.     [0]  FIND    - Finds all events that match the find criteria.                    select FIND, then press [F2] for more help.     [1]  DATE    - Changes the current CALENDAR date. Enter date                    in mm/dd/yyyy format. NOTE - does not change                     the current system date or time.     [3]  PRINT   - Prints a list of all the events for that day or                    all the events that match the find criteria.     [4]  ALARM   - Places selected events into the ALARM file to be                    reminded of them later when the alarm is on.     [5]  MERGE   - Merges two CALENDAR files. If events are selected                    it merges these events TO another file, or if no                    events are selected it merges FROM another file.!     [6]  SELECT  - Selects events by displaying them in reverse video.                    Selected events may be put into the ALARM file,                    MERGED to another file, COPIED to a document file,                    or DELETED from the current CALENDAR file.     [7]  COPY    - Copies selected events to the internal copy buffer.                    If no events have been selected then it copies the                    copy buffer TO a document file.     [8]  DELETE  - Deletes all the selected events from the file. If no                    events have been selected, it deletes the current                    event.     [9]  ADD     - Adds another event to current CALENDAR file.$                 FIND - Help Screen     To select a function, press [CLEAR] and the function number.     [0]  EQUAL   - All occurences equal to      [1]  LESS    - All occurences less than or equal to     [2]  GREATER - All occurences greater than or equal to     [3]  RESET   - resets the find criteria to previous value     [F3] RETURN  - returns with all matches of find criteria displayed.     Special characters used inside of the fields -           *  -  means ignore preceding or following characters          ?  -  means ignore only this character$